This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a generalization bound for supervised learning from GAN-synthetic data. It also involves the use of classifiers and improving classification accuracy, which are common topics in machine learning. 

Additionally, the paper involves the generation of synthetic data using GANs, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as GANs are commonly used in image and video generation. 

The paper also involves the use of synthetic data for privacy and security reasons, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). 

Furthermore, the paper involves the use of GANs for data synthesis, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as GANs are a type of deep learning model. 

Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the generalization capability of a classifier, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as generalization is an important topic in network analysis.
